snippet.textDisplay:
As a Marathi, "Bayo" is an impressive mix of Marathi folk and modern sounds. The vocals by Cyli Khare and Srushti Tawade are captivating, and Komorebi’s production brings a unique energy to the song. The fusion of genres is fresh and innovative, giving Marathi music a new global appeal.

However, as a Marathi listener, I feel the heavy electronic elements overshadow the traditional folk essence. While experimenting with new sounds is exciting, it sometimes takes away from the authenticity that Marathi folk music is known for. A bit more of the original spirit could’ve made this fusion even more powerful. Still, it’s a great attempt at modernizing the genre!
snippet.textOriginal:

However, as a Marathi listener, I feel the heavy electronic elements overshadow the traditional folk essence. While experimenting with new sounds is exciting, it sometimes takes away from the authenticity that Marathi folk music is known for. A bit more of the original spirit could’ve made this fusion even more powerful. Still, it’s a great attempt at modernizing the genre!
